### Clean Pro Solutions — End-To-End Integration Test
### Prerequisites:
### 1. VS Code "REST Client" extension or IntelliJ HTTP Client.
### 2. Run `docker-compose up --build` in the project root.
### 3. Wait for all services to appear in Eureka: http://localhost:8761

@eurekaUrl        = http://localhost:8761
@authUrl          = http://localhost:8081
@userUrl          = http://localhost:8082
@catalogUrl       = http://localhost:8083
@schedulingUrl    = http://localhost:8084
@availabilityUrl  = http://localhost:8085
@contractUrl      = http://localhost:8086
@paymentUrl       = http://localhost:8087
@ratingUrl        = http://localhost:8088
@notificationUrl  = http://localhost:8089
@chatUrl          = http://localhost:8091
@supportUrl       = http://localhost:8092
@bffUrl           = http://localhost:8080

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 0: HEALTH CHECKS
### =========================================================================

### 0.1 - Eureka Registry
GET {{eurekaUrl}}/eureka/apps
Accept: application/json

### 0.2 - BFF Health
GET {{bffUrl}}/actuator/health

### 0.3 - Auth Service Health
GET {{authUrl}}/actuator/health

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 1: AUTENTICAÇÃO (Auth Service)
### =========================================================================

### 1.1 - Register CLIENT user
### FIX #1: register now returns { "userId": "...", "email": "..." } (was void/201)
# @name registerClient
POST {{authUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "client.e2e@cleanpro.com",
  "password": "Test@1234",
  "role": "CLIENT"
}

### 1.2 - Register CONTRACTOR user
# @name registerContractor
POST {{authUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "contractor.e2e@cleanpro.com",
  "password": "Test@1234",
  "role": "CONTRACTOR"
}

### 1.3 - Login as CLIENT (capture JWT)
# @name loginClient
POST {{authUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "client.e2e@cleanpro.com",
  "password": "Test@1234"
}

### 1.4 - Login as CONTRACTOR
# @name loginContractor
POST {{authUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "contractor.e2e@cleanpro.com",
  "password": "Test@1234"
}

### 1.5 - Validate token (response contains userId in subject)
GET {{authUrl}}/auth/validate
Authorization: Bearer {{loginClient.response.body.accessToken}}

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 2: USUÁRIOS (User Service)
### =========================================================================

### 2.1 - Create CLIENT user profile
### FIX #2: field is "type" not "role" in UserRequest DTO
# @name createClientProfile
POST {{userUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authId": "{{registerClient.response.body.userId}}",
  "name": "Carlos Cliente E2E",
  "email": "client.e2e@cleanpro.com",
  "phone": "+5511999990001",
  "type": "CLIENT"
}

### 2.2 - Create CONTRACTOR user profile
# @name createContractorProfile
POST {{userUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authId": "{{registerContractor.response.body.userId}}",
  "name": "Pedro Prestador E2E",
  "email": "contractor.e2e@cleanpro.com",
  "phone": "+5511999990002",
  "type": "CONTRACTOR",
  "address": {
    "street": "Rua das Flores",
    "number": "100",
    "city": "São Paulo",
    "state": "SP",
    "zipCode": "01310-100",
    "latitude": -23.561,
    "longitude": -46.656
  }
}

### 2.3 - Get client profile by ID
GET {{userUrl}}/users/{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}

### 2.4 - Update contractor professional profile
PUT {{userUrl}}/users/{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}/contractor-profile
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bio": "Especialista em limpeza residencial com 10 anos de experiência",
  "specialties": ["Limpeza Residencial", "Limpeza Comercial"],
  "hourlyRate": 80.00,
  "yearsOfExperience": 10
}

### 2.5 - Find nearby contractors (geospatial)
### FIX #3: params are "lat", "lng", "type" — NOT "latitude", "longitude", "role"
GET {{userUrl}}/users/nearby?lat=-23.561&lng=-46.656&radiusKm=10&type=CONTRACTOR

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 3: CATÁLOGO (Catalog Service)
### =========================================================================

### 3.1 - Create a service offering
### FIX #5: field is "durationInHours" (int 1-24), NOT "estimatedDurationMinutes"
### "active" is not a field of ServiceRequest; remove it
# @name createService
POST {{catalogUrl}}/services
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Limpeza Residencial Completa",
  "description": "Limpeza completa de imóvel residencial incluindo todos os cômodos",
  "type": "CLEANING",
  "basePrice": 200.00,
  "durationInHours": 4
}

### 3.2 - List all active services
### FIX #4: /services/active does not exist — correct route is /services?activeOnly=true
GET {{catalogUrl}}/services?activeOnly=true

### 3.3 - Search services by keyword
GET {{catalogUrl}}/services/search?query=limpeza

### 3.4 - Get service by ID
GET {{catalogUrl}}/services/{{createService.response.body.id}}

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 4: DISPONIBILIDADE (Availability Service)
### =========================================================================

### 4.1 - Check contractor availability for a time slot
### FIX #6: endpoint returns raw Boolean (true/false), not { "available": bool }
### Note: query params are contractorId, startTime, endTime
GET {{availabilityUrl}}/availability/check?contractorId={{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}&startTime=2026-06-01T10:00:00Z&endTime=2026-06-01T14:00:00Z

### 4.2 - Get all slots for contractor
GET {{availabilityUrl}}/availability/contractor/{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 5: AGENDAMENTO (Scheduling Service)
### =========================================================================

### 5.1 - Create a scheduling (recurrencePattern optional; NONE or omit)
# @name createSchedule
POST {{schedulingUrl}}/schedulings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": "{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "contractorId": "{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "serviceId": "{{createService.response.body.id}}",
  "startTime": "2026-06-01T10:00:00Z",
  "endTime": "2026-06-01T14:00:00Z",
  "recurrencePattern": "NONE"
}

### 5.2 - Get scheduling by ID
GET {{schedulingUrl}}/schedulings/{{createSchedule.response.body.id}}

### 5.3 - Get all schedulings for the client
GET {{schedulingUrl}}/schedulings/client/{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}

### 5.4 - Create a recurring scheduling (WEEKLY)
### FIX #7: "occurrences" is a @RequestParam in the URL, NOT a field in the request body
POST {{schedulingUrl}}/schedulings/recurring?occurrences=4
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": "{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "contractorId": "{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "serviceId": "{{createService.response.body.id}}",
  "startTime": "2026-06-08T10:00:00Z",
  "endTime": "2026-06-08T14:00:00Z",
  "recurrencePattern": "WEEKLY"
}

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 6: CONTRATO (Contract Service → SAGA Init)
### =========================================================================

### 6.1 - Create a contract (triggers ContractCreatedEvent → payment-service)
# @name createContract
POST {{contractUrl}}/contracts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": "{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "contractorId": "{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "serviceId": "{{createService.response.body.id}}",
  "schedulingId": "{{createSchedule.response.body.id}}",
  "agreedPrice": 250.00
}

### 6.2 - Get contract by ID (should be PENDING_PAYMENT)
GET {{contractUrl}}/contracts/{{createContract.response.body.id}}

### 6.3 - List contracts for client
GET {{contractUrl}}/contracts/client/{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 7: PAGAMENTO (Payment Service → SAGA Complete)
### =========================================================================

### 7.1 - Check payment created by SAGA (wait ~2s after contract creation)
GET {{paymentUrl}}/payments/contract/{{createContract.response.body.id}}

### 7.2 - Simulate payment gateway webhook (approval)
POST {{paymentUrl}}/payments/webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "externalTransactionId": "txn_stripe_e2e_001",
  "contractId": "{{createContract.response.body.id}}",
  "success": true
}

### 7.3 - Verify contract changed to CONFIRMED (wait ~3s for SAGA propagation)
GET {{contractUrl}}/contracts/{{createContract.response.body.id}}

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 8: NOTIFICAÇÕES (Notification Service)
### =========================================================================

### 8.1 - Get notifications for client (created by SAGA events)
GET {{notificationUrl}}/notifications/recipient/{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}

### 8.2 - Get notifications for contractor
GET {{notificationUrl}}/notifications/recipient/{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 9: CHAT (Chat Service — Real-time Messaging)
### =========================================================================

### 9.1 - Get or create chat room for the contract
# @name createRoom
POST {{chatUrl}}/chat/rooms?clientId={{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}&contractorId={{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}&contractId={{createContract.response.body.id}}

### 9.2 - Send a message from client
POST {{chatUrl}}/chat/{{createRoom.response.body}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "senderId": "{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "content": "Olá! Confirma o serviço para amanhã às 10h?"
}

### 9.3 - Send a reply from contractor
POST {{chatUrl}}/chat/{{createRoom.response.body}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "senderId": "{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "content": "Olá! Confirmado, estarei aí pontualmente."
}

### 9.4 - Get message history
GET {{chatUrl}}/chat/{{createRoom.response.body}}/messages

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 10: AVALIAÇÃO (Rating Service)
### =========================================================================

### 10.1 - Client rates the contractor
POST {{ratingUrl}}/ratings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reviewerId": "{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "reviewedId": "{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "contractId": "{{createContract.response.body.id}}",
  "score": 5,
  "comment": "Excelente profissional! Serviço impecável e dentro do prazo."
}

### 10.2 - Get ratings for contractor
GET {{ratingUrl}}/ratings/reviewed/{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}

### 10.3 - Get average score for contractor
### FIX #8: returns raw Double (e.g. 5.0), NOT an object like { "averageScore": 5.0 }
GET {{ratingUrl}}/ratings/reviewed/{{createContractorProfile.response.body.id}}/average

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 11: SUPORTE (Support Service)
### =========================================================================

### 11.1 - Open a support ticket
### FIX #9: TicketRequest requires "priority" (@NotNull) and "subject" (@NotBlank)
# @name openTicket
POST {{supportUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requesterId": "{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}",
  "contractId": "{{createContract.response.body.id}}",
  "type": "DISPUTE",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "subject": "Atraso do prestador sem aviso prévio",
  "description": "O prestador chegou com 1 hora de atraso sem comunicação prévia."
}

### 11.2 - Get ticket by ID
GET {{supportUrl}}/tickets/{{openTicket.response.body.id}}

### 11.3 - List tickets for client
GET {{supportUrl}}/tickets/requester/{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}

### 11.4 - Assign ticket to support agent
PATCH {{supportUrl}}/tickets/{{openTicket.response.body.id}}/assign

### 11.5 - Resolve ticket
PATCH {{supportUrl}}/tickets/{{openTicket.response.body.id}}/resolve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resolution": "Contatamos o prestador e foi confirmado o atraso. Aplicamos desconto de 15% ao cliente."
}

### 11.6 - Close ticket
PATCH {{supportUrl}}/tickets/{{openTicket.response.body.id}}/close

### =========================================================================
### ETAPA 12: BFF (API Gateway verification)
### =========================================================================

### 12.1 - BFF health (confirms all downstream services reachable via Eureka)
GET {{bffUrl}}/actuator/health

### 12.2 - Access auth service via BFF
POST {{bffUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "client.e2e@cleanpro.com",
  "password": "Test@1234"
}

### 12.3 - Access scheduling service via BFF
GET {{bffUrl}}/schedulings/client/{{createClientProfile.response.body.id}}
